overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by integrating a database, an admin dashboard, and an
  authentication system. The assistant evaluated the existing codebase,
  clarified requirements for demographic data and authentication complexity, and
  developed a comprehensive plan. The implementation involved updating
  demographic fields, creating a Prisma model for questionnaire responses, and
  building API endpoints for data submission, retrieval, and CSV export. A
  simple password-based authentication system was set up using Next.js
  middleware to protect admin routes and API access. The admin dashboard was
  developed to allow clients to view and download responses. During testing,
  direct API calls confirmed the robust functionality of the database and
  authentication, although a minor UI issue prevented direct form submission
  from the browser after pre-filling. All core features were successfully
  implemented and verified.
